post_text:
It's that time of year when we are looking for more parents, grandparents, members of the community, etc... to become part of the 50 member voting board of the Little Giant Booster Club. We meet the 2nd Wednesday of the month at 6:30pm in the CHS cafeteria. As part of this, you have a voice in how the money we raise is distributed. We also ask that you volunteer to work concession stands throughout the year. The majority of the money that we are able to distribute among the athletic programs is brought in through the concession stands.
If you would like to be part of the club please comment below. Or contact the 2019-2020 officers: Co-presidents-Samantha Norton & Kim Turner, Vice President-Stephanie Smith, Secretary-Amanda Becker, Treasurer-Julie Reeder
Trustees: Ashley Munson, Jennifer Kees, Amy Smith and Jenniffer Swank
Thank you!!

The Alumni Football game Canton vs. Richwoods will be played in Canton on August 12th. Game time is 7pm. The new scoreboard will also be revealed and dedicated to the 2016-2017 Canton High School Football team.

The Booster Club will need many volunteers to help with various things.

Gates will open to the public between 500-530pm.
There will be 2 shifts
1. 445pm-645pm
2. 645pm - close

We need 4 people/shift for 50/50 and 10 people/shift for concession stand (possibly more if we decide to do a separate drink tent to help avoid congestion at the stand) and 2 people for the 2nd shift for tshirt sales.

Please contact Andra Chamberlin 338-7772 if you are able to help!

post_text:
It's that time of year when we are looking for more parents, grandparents, members of the community, etc... to become part of the 50 member voting board of the Little Giant Booster Club. We meet the 2nd Wednesday of the month at 6:30pm in the CHS cafeteria. As part of this, you have a voice in how the money we raise is distributed. We also ask that you volunteer to work concession stands throughout the year. The majority of the money that we are able to distribute among the athletic programs is brought in through the concession stands. We also have the Secretary position open for the upcoming school year.
If you would like to be part of the board please comment below. Or contact the following members of the membership committee: Wendy Atchley, Connie Shawgo or Samantha Norton. Or any of the current officers: Andra Chamberlin, Angie Miller, Amanda Becker or Carla Postin.

Thank you!!
